<div id="review_4372098021" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4372098021" />
    <a title="Auntie Terror" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/63716836-auntie-terror"><img alt="Auntie Terror" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1629470051p2/63716836.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4372098021?book_show_action=true">Dec 15, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Auntie Terror" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Auntie Terror" href="/user/show/63716836-auntie-terror">Auntie Terror</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Audiobook " href="/book/show/58787068-nervous-conditions">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/63716836-auntie-terror?shelf=audiobooks">audiobooks</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4372098021" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2839337222453030402">This is an amazing book, reminiscent of Achebe&apos;s trilogy, but from a woman&apos;s perspective - which, frankly, just adds another layer of discrimination. The narrative tone is starkly and heartbreakingly honest and reflected. And the narrator voicing it is brilliant, too.</span>
  <span id="freeText2839337222453030402" style="display:none">This is an amazing book, reminiscent of Achebe's trilogy, but from a woman's perspective - which, frankly, just adds another layer of discrimination. The narrative tone is starkly and heartbreakingly honest and reflected. And the narrator voicing it is brilliant, too.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2839337222453030402" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

